  "texts": [
    "Automating all aspects of everyday interactions with animals may lead to deskilling livestock professionals' expertise in animal care.",
    "Further, elimination of direct or regular contact with animals may lead to \"dehumanization\" of animals and degradation of moral concern for them (145, 146).",
    "These pitfalls are likely to affect technologies designed for farm animals as well.",
    "Therefore, it is imperative that such technologies are designed to complement, rather than substitute, human-animal interactions, and to support human-animal relations.",
    "This requires input from the various human caregiving roles that are essential to ensuring animals' welfare is truly prioritized (147)."
  ],
